The construction site of Brunelleschi's Dome: men and machines|https://duomo.firenze.it/en/opera-magazine/post/6296/the-construction-site-of-brunelleschi-s-dome-men-and-machines|during the Middle Ages,  ...    These machines and the materials transported had to be maneuver and put in place by expert workers. There were only about sixty masters involved in the construction under the guidance of Brunelleschi. The architect knew well how much dangerous it was to work at those dizzying altitudes and made sure that during the sixteen years of construction (1420-1436) his masters could work safely. There are records of “only” eight seriously workers injured, one “white death”: that of Nencio di Chello who died falling from the walls of the drum in 1422 and other injuries from falling materials or from moving construction machines… but, it still something incredible for that period! This is thanks to the fact that Brunelleschi and the Opera del Duomo had taken very modern precautions: the large  ...    and those who did it received wages increased, in proportion to the risk. The history of the Dome Construction site shows that the genius of Brunelleschi and the
